uripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 570 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πίει, πίεις, Kretschmer [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Griech. Vaseninschr.” p.195\">Refs</a>]; <i>infinitive</i> πιεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.70, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.172, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; later <i>contraction</i> πεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 11.140 (1st c.AD: Lucillius Epigrammaticus), “Mim.Oxy.” 413.66, “PMag.Lond.” 121.738, “PFlor.” 101.8 (1st c.AD), etc.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <i>Epic dialect</i> πῐέμεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.378, πιέειν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.263, πιέναι\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <i>falsa lectio</i> for{ὑπιέναι} in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 5.18 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i> πῐών, πῐοῦσα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.102, etc., πῐέουσα 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 7.11 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, <i>subjunctive</i> πινώμεθα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hermippus Comicus 25; _imperative_ πίνεο 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “Theriaca” 912 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <b>πίομαι</b> [ῑ] as <i>present</i> <i>middle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Ibycus Lyricus 17 (assuming variant), 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.86, and so ἐκπίομαι [ῑ] 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 199, ἐμπίομαι [ῐ] 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1129 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] (<i>passive</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 5.43 (2nd-3rd c.AD: Rufinus Epigrammaticus))\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.312, 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Aër.” 9, etc.: _Epic dialect_ \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>imperfect</i> πίνετο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 9.45.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] —Other tenses are from πω- or πο-, <i>perfect</i> πέπωκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 821, etc.:\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> ποθήσομαι (κατα-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 1502, (ἐκ-) 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.240e: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἐπόθην (ἐξ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 66, (κατ-) 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 111d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> <i>infinitive</i> πεπόσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 477 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]: <i>Aeolic dialect</i> <i>present</i> <b>πώνω</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 20, 52, “Supp.” 20.3: \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> <i>imperative</i> πῶθι, τῶ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Etymologicum Magnum” 698.52 \">Refs</a>]. [ῑ always in πίνω. πίνομα; ῐ always in <i>aorist</i> ἔπιον, hence πίε must be read for πῖνε in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 11.19 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus), and ἔπῑνον for ἔπιον in “Anacreontea” 5.5: 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus has ἐθέλουσι δὲ πῑέμεν ἄμφω 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.825, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 18.3; but καὶ φαγέμεν πῐέμεν τε 15.378 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; in <i>imperative</i> πῖθι, ῑ always.—In <i>future</i> πίομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus and Trag. use ῑ, 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 13.493, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 578, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 622, compare 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 962, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1289, 1401, “fragment” 311; but ῐ in lon Lyric poetry 2.10 (nisi to be read πιέτω), (ἐκ-) 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Comicus 9, 5th-6th c.BC: Amipsias Comicus 22 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also in later Poetry, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 11.8,25.5 (1st c.AD: Apollonides Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; for <i>present</i> <i>middle</i> πίομαι, see above]: —<b>drink</b>, frequently from [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus downwards, with _accusative_, π. οἶνον, ὐρόν, αἷμα, etc., 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.391, 17.225, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 622, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. ὕδωρ Αἰσήποιο <b>drink</b> its water, i.e. live on its banks, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.825, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.86 (_middle_)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>genitive</i> <i>partitive</i>, <b>drink of</b> a thing, π. οἴνοιο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 22.11 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εἰς οἶνον.., ἔνθεν ἔπινον <b>whereof</b>..,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.220; αἵματος ὄφρα πίω 11.96, compare 15.373 \">Refs</a>]; also πίνειν κρητῆρας οῐνοιο <b>to drink</b> bowls of wine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 8.232; κύπελλα ὄνου 4.346 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἀπὸ κρήνης <b>drink</b> of a spring, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 959 (but κρήνης 962)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἀπ᾽ αὐτοῦ (i.e. δέπαος) αἴθοπα οἶνον <b>from</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.226; δέπα ἔνθεν ἔπινον 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.62; ἐκ κεράμων μέθυ πίνετο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.469; ἐκ τῆς χειρὸς διδοῖ πιεῖν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.172; ἐκ ταὐτοῦ.. ποτηρίου 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1289; ἐξ ἀργύρου ἢ χρυσοῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 417a; ἀπὸ τοῦ ποταμοῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 4.5.4 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σκύφος ᾧ περ ἔπινεν <b>with</b> which.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.112 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; π. κερατίνοις ποτηρίοις variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 6.1.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ φάρμακα π. παρὰ τοῦ ἰατροῦ draughts sent by him, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 467c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>drink</b>, ἐσθιέμεν καὶ πινέμεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.305; ὁ πῖνε καὶ ἦσθε 5.94, 6.249, compare 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 24.476, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; μῆλα πιόμεν᾽ ἐκ βοτάνης <b>going to drink</b> after pasture,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 13.493; πρὸς βίαν πώνην 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 20; πῖνε, πῖν᾽ ἐπὶ συμφοραῖς 4th-5th c.BC: Simonides Lyricus 14; π. πρὸς ἡδονήν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 176e; εἰς μέθην [prev. author] “Lg.” 775b; διδόναι πιεῖν 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 124; πιεῖν αἰτεῖν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.3.41 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; τινὶ πιεῖν ἐγχέας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 1.3.9; πιεῖν τις ἡμῖν ἐγχεάτω 4th-3rd c.BC: Philemo Comicus 9: in \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>perfect</i> πέπωκα, <b>to be drunk</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Cyclops” 536 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πίνοντά τε καὶ πεπωκότα <b>drinking</b> and <b>having finished drinking</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 117c. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>celebrate by a carouse</b>, νίκην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “de gymnastica” 54. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>drink up</b>, as the earth does rain, τὸ ὕδωρ, ὄμβρον, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.117, 4.198; πιοῦσα κόνις μέλαν αἷμα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 979 (Lyric poetry), compare “Th.” 736 (Lyric poetry), 821, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1401 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of plants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Symposium” 2.25 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of a lamp, π. τοὔλαιον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Cat.” 27; λύχνος.. πολλὰ πιὼν μέλη “Anthologia Graeca” 5.196 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus, uncertain reading). (I.- 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>pōy</b>- and <b>pī</b>-, cf. Sanskrit <i>pāy-áyati</i> 'cause to drink', <b>pīti</b>- 'a drink', Latin <i>pōtus</i>, etc.)","strongNumber":"G4095","accentedUnicode":"πίνω","shortDef":"to drink","mediumDef":"<b>to drink,</b> <ref='Mat.6.25, 31; 26:27, 29'>Mt. 6:25, 31; 26:27, 29</ref>, and frequently ; troponym of the earth, <b>to drink in, imbibe,</b> <ref='Heb.6.7'>Heb. 6:7</ref>","stepGloss":"to drink","stepTransliteration":"pinō","count":75,"_es_Definition":"beber","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 飲用<br>2) 與\"杯\"連用,表示承受艱辛的考驗或死亡 (太20:22,26:42;可10:38;約18:11)<br>   (啟14:10,18:3)有類似的意思","_zh_Definition":"1) 饮用<br>2) 与\"杯\"连用,表示承受艰辛的考验或死亡(太20:22,26:42;可10:38;约18:11)<br> (启14:10 ,18:3)有类似的意思","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"uống.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"喝","_es_Gloss":"beber","_zh_Gloss":"喝"}]}